rComments: I recommend taking courses with Prof IKA.

Contrary from what I hear from other people, I found Professor Ika just fine. Maybe it was because project management really interested me. That being said, classes are participative, but sometimes it can be dry. Just sometimes though. Grading criteria not clear at all. He knows the material and the field very well. Only 12 students in French.
Get ready to have a stare-down contest with this man. He is a good professor who knows what he is talking about, but definitely gives you a weird vibe.

Awful, think himself as a biggest person in PM. Doesn't care about others people's view, not friendly with disagreement/different opinion, Grades depend of him liking you and zero field experience. Work doesn't count if he doesn't agree with you and give you lame feedbacks and biased to some people. Game me a B just because i miss few lectures.
